<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-26T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-26T11:00:00-05:00" n="608" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d608">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/2269: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vigo</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Corcoran</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vigo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-26T16:00:00+00:00">July 26, 1936—4
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 26—1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Military authorities as result of public insult offered me in street
                                by uniformed armed Fascist in company with others have broadcast <pb facs="0744" n="645" xml:id="pg_645"/> public apology following
                                vigorous protest. Representatives of republics regarded by Fascists
                                and certain of military as enemies in the same class as Communist
                                extremists. Feel more secure as result of incident and apology.
                                Conduct Vice Consul Stewart and staff admirable. Situation tense but
                                believe military willing and able at present to protect us and our
                                families.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Corcoran</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>